  <caaml:metaData>
    <caaml:comment>10cm of new snow over a light wind crust over the 40cm of new snow that fell on the 6/8/18.&#13;
size 1 to 2 natural avalanches had run during the storm and had released on steep, high SE aspects.&#13;
A larger, 2.5, but isolated, steep,  south aspect, natural avalanche had released from beneath an ice fall. The failure layer appeared to be the new/old bond from the 6/8/18 storm which then stepped down to basal blue ice.&#13;
However the new snow seems to be bonding with time and stability was good generally, although caution is needed on steep, shady unsupported slopes. </caaml:comment>
